    vtrans:"karmaṇy evādhikāras te mā phaleṣu kadācana",
    veng:"You have a right to perform your prescribed duties, but you are not entitled to the fruits of your actions. Never consider yourself the cause of the results of your activities, and never be attached to not doing your duty.",
    insight:"Perhaps the most famous verse in the Gita. Do your work sincerely but don't obsess over results. This is the foundation of Karma Yoga and one of the most practical spiritual principles ever articulated.",
    kid:"Krishna said: 'Do your very best at everything you do — but don't worry too much about whether you win or lose. Just do your best and let God handle the rest!' This is one of the most important lessons about life. It means: try your hardest, do your duty, and don't stress about the result.",
